Bauchi State Government has disclosed plans to establish isolation centers in three selected hospitals for the treatment and control of Lassa fever across the state. Governor Bala Mohammed, said yesterday when he received officials of Nigeria Center for Disease Control (NCDC) in Bauchi, adding that already the state government has taken proactive measures against the spread of the disease by setting-up an emergency outbreak basket fund. Responding, NCDC Director General, Dr. Chikwe Ihekweazu, represented by the agencyâ€™s Director Administration and Human Resources, Alhaji Yakubu Abdullahi, said the visit was to commiserate with the state over the death of the late Katukan Bauchi and others who lost their lives after contracting Lassa fever disease. FG: 25,000 made in Nigeria vehicles ready this year FG approves draft policy for Parks reform Oyetola sends Amotekun bill to Osun Assembly